      "message": "Can we use \u0027rem\u0027 units instead? Longer explanation follows:\n\nUsing percentages is not the suggested way of achieving consistent font sizes, because they suffer from compounding problem. In other words, percentages are calculated with respect to their parent\u0027s font-size. So for example, if the \u003cinput\u003e\u0027s parent chain has a different font-size than the #slash parent\u0027s chain, the 81% evaluates to different absolute values for each.\n\nInstead \u0027rem\u0027 units are much easier to use, because they only depend on the \u003chtml\u003e element\u0027s font-size. See more info at https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size#Rems.",
